Description: A Potion of Cleansing can be used to remove all negative effects applied to a player, like Poison
If you are killed at night whilst in the possession of an Ankh of Reincarnation, you will be revived a day later

DetailedDescription: It's clear this tiny statue once shimmered and was likely worth a fortune, but its faded beauty belies a corruption that has since taken hold of it.
No matter how much you try to buff the putrid dirt and grease from it, you can't seem to get it clean.
The filth soaks every cloth you use and you can almost feel the foul substance covering the idol oozing into - no, not into - through - your hands
Yet still you cannot shake the idea that this old thing has some hidden power and might be worth holding onto.
Holding this item incurs a 33% chance of being Decayed at the start of the day (Decay can stack)
Holding this item grants a 10% chance of creating a single Potion of {Cleansing, Poison, Protection or Weakness} at the start of the day
If a Lich holds this item, they have a 50% chance of generating a new Lich Spell at the start of the day
There may be multiple copies of this item, and each morning tick is independent per copy of the item
